\pard\plain \fi360\sa160\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The success of this final test was recognized by another pronouncement of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s covenant promises for Abraham. God reaffirmed His promise to bless Abraham with descendants as numerous as the stars in the sky, and to bless the entire world through Abraham\u8217\'92s offspring. Just as it began, the story of Abraham ends with this promise of worldwide blessing (Gen 12:3; 22:18).}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s initial promise to Abraham appeared unconditional. Nothing was required of Abraham for him to receive this blessing. However, over the course of multiple reiterations of the promise, God established that Abraham\u8217\'92s faithful obedience was a condition of his continued blessing. The test to sacrifice Isaac was the final proof of Abraham\u8217\'92s commitment to cling to God\u8217\'92s voice and follow His promise, no matter where it led or what it required (Gen 22:18).\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Grigoni, M. R., Custis, M., Mangum, D., & Whitehead, M. M. (2012). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/csabraham?ref=Bible.Ge21.1-21&off=15389&ctx=verses+of+Psa+118.%0a%0a~The+success+of+this+"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Abraham: Following God\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92s Promise\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Ge 21:1\endash 22:24). Bellingham, WA: Lexham Press.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
