\par\pard\plain \sa160\sb360\ql\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs32\b0\i0 Application}
\par\pard\plain \sa160\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s life is bracketed by examples of extreme faith. In Genesis 12:1, God told him to go to a foreign land, and in Gen 12:4, he obeyed without question. He left all he knew for the sake of obtaining God\u8217\'92s promise. In Genesis 22, after he finally received the promised son, Abraham was commanded to give Isaac up as a burnt offering. Despite the apparent absurdity of the request, Abraham complied without ever questioning God. He was confident that both he and Isaac would return\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 whether by resurrection or some other form of deliverance (see Heb 11:19).\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Grigoni, M. R., Custis, M., Mangum, D., & Whitehead, M. M. (2012). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/csabraham?ref=Bible.Ge21.1-21&off=22598"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Abraham: Following God\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92s Promise\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Ge 21:1\endash 22:24). Bellingham, WA: Lexham Press.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sa160\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Despite his failures along the way, Abraham is remembered for these two successes\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 particularly his unflinching faith in Gen 22. After walking with God for 25 years, Abraham knew God could be trusted. Sacrificing Isaac wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t the first seemingly \u8220\'93crazy\u8221\'94 thing God asked him to do. God had commanded Abraham to leave the comforts of home and spend his life sojourning in tents; He had instructed him to travel with his family among potentially hostile enemies; He had ordered him to circumcise himself as a sign of His covenant of \u8220\'93blessing\u8221\'94; He had directed him to cast out his true firstborn son, Ishmael; and He had told him to conceive a child at the age of 100. Yet Abraham trusted God\u8217\'92s purposes through all these things and, in Gen 22, he complied without hesitation with God\u8217\'92s most shocking demand yet.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 Not only was God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s reputation for keeping His covenant at stake\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 He would have to undergo something similar in the future. Approximately 2,000 years later, in a situation that mirrored Abraham\u8217\'92s, God offered His own Son as a sacrifice for the sins of humanity. This connection is what makes Gen 22 so real for us. Abraham could have looked for an easy way out just as he did earlier in his life, but he didn\u8217\'92t. He had come to know God\u8217\'92s power and trusted Him to fulfill His promises.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Grigoni, M. R., Custis, M., Mangum, D., & Whitehead, M. M. (2012). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/csabraham?ref=Bible.Ge21.1-21&off=23337&ctx=+(see+Heb+11:19).%0a+%0a~Despite+his+failures"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Abraham: Following God\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92s Promise\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Ge 21:1\endash 22:24). Bellingham, WA: Lexham Press.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 God commands us to trust in the sacrifice of His Son, and this can sometimes be difficult. There are certainly easier ways to get through life\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 ways that will allow for the kind of compromise and dishonesty that we observed earlier in Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s story. But none of these will get us where God wants us to be: with Him for eternity. Walter Brueggemann, a theologian and Bible commentator, summed up the situation well:}
\par\pard\plain \li360\sa160\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 The testing times for Israel and for all of us who are heirs of Abraham are those times when it is seductively attractive to find an easier, less demanding alternative to God. The testings which come in history (and which are from God) drive us to find out whether we mean what we say about our faith being grounded solely in the gospel.}
\par\pard\plain \sa160\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Following God is difficult, but Abraham knew he could trust God no matter what kind of test emerged. The same is true for us today. When our commitment is tested, we can look to examples like Abraham for the courage to persevere (see Rom 15:4; 1 Cor 10:11; Heb 12:1\endash 3). The same God who provided for Abraham in his most desperate hour (see Gen 22:13) also makes deliverance possible for us (see John 3:16\endash 17). As true children of Abraham\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 followers of God characterized by faith\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 we can demonstrate our devotion by an extreme faith in God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promises and sacrifice.}
